title: The Survival Battle Royale That Couldn't Survive

media:group.media:title: The Survival Battle Royale That Couldn't Survive
media:group.media:description:
Over the years, Battle Royales have gotten bigger, louder, and faster. Lobby sizes have ballooned. The pace of matches has increased. Maps have grown to the size of small countries. To say the least, Battle Royales have gotten big. But not everyone was content to create games that trend toward a larger scale. Some wanted to take the genre back to its roots, by creating a smaller, more intimate survival environment in which you hunt your peers. Todayâ€™s video follows this trend. To create a game centered around tracking enemies and engaging in close-quarters combat. This is Darwin Project.
